    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-26T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-26T05:00:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.00B Communist International of Youth/16:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-26T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 26, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 26—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>439. Sixth Congress of Communist International of Youth opened in Moscow
                    September 25th. Following United States delegates were elected to Presidium:
                        <persName corresp="#p_GG1">Green</persName>, <persName>Lightfoot</persName>
                    and <persName>Porter</persName>. <persName>Pieck</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DG1">Dimitrov</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KOW1"
                        >Kuusinen</persName> were present at the first session. <persName>Raymond
                        Guillot [<hi rend="italic">Guyot</hi>]</persName> (French) made opening
                    speech.</p>
                <p>Embassy will follow sessions closely.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
